!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

agreement /əˈɡriːmənt/

(agreements) 

1. N-COUNT An agreement is a formal decision about future action that is made by two or more countries, groups, or people. 协议 

例： It looks as though a compromise agreement has now been reached. 看起来好像现在已经达成了一个妥协协议。 

2. N-UNCOUNT Agreement on something is a joint decision that a particular course of action should be taken. 共识 

例： A spokesman said, however, that the two men had not reached agreement on the issues discussed. 但是，一位发言人说这两个人对讨论的问题还未达成共识。 

3. N-UNCOUNT Agreement with someone means having the same opinion as they have. 同意 

例： The judge kept nodding in agreement. 法官不断点头表示同意。 

4. PHRASE If you are in agreement with someone, you have the same opinion as they have. 意见相同 

5. N-UNCOUNT Agreement to a course of action means allowing it to happen or giving it your approval. 许可 

例： The clinic doctor will then write to your doctor to get his agreement. 临床医生会给你的大夫写信取得他的许可。

